headline: HIV Drug Makers Get Spooked by Possible Trump Cut, but Impact Looks Manageable
summary: Gilead Sciences has been one of the best-performing large biotech companies over the past year, rising about 50%.  Shares of both Gilead and GSK, another HIV-focused drugmaker, fell after The Wall Street Journal reported the administration was considering drastic cuts to funding for domestic HIV prevention.  Perhaps more important is that the potential cuts come as investors are increasingly worried about broader potential reductions to Medicaid, which could impact access to HIV drugs.

headline: Gilead Stock Falls on Report Trump Administration Wants to Cut HIV-Prevention Funding
summary: Gilead Sciences  stock declined Wednesday after The Wall Street Journal reported the Department of Health and Human Services was considering federal funding cuts to domestic HIV prevention.  The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, an arm of the HHS, has a Division of HIV Prevention dating back to the 1980s.  In addition to tracking HIV infections across the country, it focuses on community outreach, working with state and local leaders to promote testing and prevention.
